By @islandboiphotography

Honesty post. 🙏🏾🫶🏾
About a two months ago, I was in an accident on a @bird scooter.  The brakes weren’t functioning properly and I tried to stop it by putting my foot down. It lunged me forward and I cracked my chin so hard, when I became conscious my friend was screaming my name, tears in his eyes, pressing on my chest and the ambulance was pulling up.
When I got to the hospital I needed a MRI on my brain, neck and spine. The doctor came in and had to get my permission for the radiation because I was pregnant 😭 We had no idea.
Thank God, there was no serious damage besides not being able to open my mouth fully, physical scars and some knee damage. I was able to leave that night, with the nurses clapping and saying “you’re lucky, those scooter accidents are always much worse.” I would say blessed and highly favored.
The following week, we found out I was having a miscarriage 😢😢😢 which was devastating to say the least. All while putting together my First Annual Fundaiser for my nonprofit @voicesbeyondassault I had to power through knowing I now have an Angel baby.
I gathered the strength and will to still make the event happen because this organization is my purpose! The morning of the fundraiser, the miscarriage started 🤧. I questioned, why that day??? But why not! That feminine energy powered through and so did God. We had incredible event with such great energy including having my loving family right by my side and we raised 25K 🙏🏾
Through the pain, I continued to smile, give thanks, love on my people, and even post memes on here 🥴 No one having a clue of what I was going through 
I’m just saying this to say, things can change in a blink of an eye. Value yourself, those you love and be forever grateful for what you have and mostly the life you get to LIVE.

I’m so much better and living fully like before but with more grace. Just wanted to express that through tragedy there is always triumph 🥂

Love y’all!

~Brianna Michelle 💕

April 1st is a day I will always and forever celebrate how far I’ve come.  This day in college, I was strangled, raped and kidnapped for hours. It changed who I thought I would be and the trajectory of my life.  I been through the fire on my healing journey but walked into my light. I did so with God within me, the support of my Mother, family, friends and the will the survive past the internal pain of trauma.
As a survivor, I’ve learned the journey to self love, the importance of compassion for self and others, being nonjudgmental, and that healing is not an easy journey but it’s worth it.  I’m an example that ‘healing looks good on YOU!’ 
Because of my healing, I have been able to start a nonprofit organization that is dedicated to empowering the lives of survivors of sexual violence and create safe, healing and survivorships experiences that I wish I had.  @voicesbeyondassault is growing so beautifully because I do it because of pure love.  It is what I lead with nowadays because it will live on to be my legacy!
This month is also #sexualassaultawareness month and I hope that you all support and believe survivors! I pray that survivors give themselves more love and compassion this month, take self care days and embody their power! I love you sisters, brothers and non-binary survivors.  This month is ours!
~Brianna Michelle
#rapesurvivor #survivor #healer #believesurvivors #lover #voicesbeyondassault

As Women our bodies are always changing. 
Right now, this is the heaviest I’ve been in my life, I’m at 160lbs. Most of it is love and happy weight: eating out a lot, traveling, not boxing or working out and other times just being lazy. My mind played some tricks on me and
I’ve been critical of myself at times because of work, not fitting my jeans or shorts, having a roll when I sit down, someone mentioning “you’ve gained weight,” and sometimes looking at old photos 😩🥴😂 
However, I’m HERE! I’m in the I LOVE MY BODY stage and accepting all that I am, where I’m at and taking care of ME! Getting back in the gym, eating better, and just tightening up some of the thickness because I  ain’t mad at the curves 😛 
It’s ME season and that includes loving ME for ME and celebrating every stage of my life and body because I’m able and healthy 🤲🏾

They say good things come to those who wait. I been real patient 🛸
As I’m getting back in shape, the first pic is how I think I look but that second slide is me 😩😂

This hit my spirit!🙏🏾
When I tell you my patience is thin with some things and people (I’m working on it 🥴) BUT with God, I KNOW I’m promised everything that he has put in my heart and that I actively seek. 
When my mind starts playing tricks on me and I’m feeling like I’m behind or doing some things later in life, I pray through those thoughts. Because what does that even mean? That’s societal thoughts and perceptions, it’s not of God.
I know that when I walk in God's favor, His blessings will chase me down and I WILL blossom in all my passions. I’ve never quit on what fuels my heart because I know BIG GOD got me. I will create a new narrative and vision for others.
It’s never how you start the race but how you finish. I’m playing God’s game and on his calendar! So my patience is different.
I hope you have the love and faith in God to never give up on you. It’s not always easy but it’s worth it, you’re worth it! God will never give up on you, so never give up on God and His miraculous power. But also remember, if you really want to get God's attention, put actions behind what you believe in. 🙏🏾🥰❤️

#god #patience #nevertoolate #keepgoing #trustgod #trustyourself #friday #letsgo
